  "prompt": "How many pictures does a 2GB SD card hold?",
  "response": "The number of pictures a 2GB SD card can hold depends on the resolution and file size of the images. Here are some approximate estimates:\n\n1. **Low-resolution images (1-2 megapixels)**: These images typically range from 500KB to 1MB in size. With this size, a 2GB SD card can hold around 2000 to 4000 pictures.\n\n2. **Medium-resolution images (5-8 megapixels)**: These images typically range from 1MB to 4MB in size. With this size, a 2GB SD card can hold around 500 to 2000 pictures.\n\n3. **High-resolution images (10-20 megapixels)**: These images typically range from 5MB to 10MB in size. With this size, a 2GB SD card can hold around 200 to 400 pictures.\n\n4. **Very high-resolution images (20+ megapixels)**: These images typically range from 10MB to 25MB or more in size. With this size, a 2GB SD card can hold around 80 to 200 pictures.\n\nRemember that these are rough estimates and actual numbers can vary based on file format, compression settings, and additional data being stored on the SD card.",
